{{distinguish|UK HealthCare}}

'''Healthcare UK''' is an agency of the British government which promotes the UK healthcare sector to overseas markets and supports healthcare partnerships between the UK and overseas healthcare providers.  It is a joint initiative between the [[Department of Health (United Kingdom)|Department of Health]], [[UK Trade & Investment]] and [[NHS England]], with offices in London.<ref>{{cite web|title=Healthcare UK homepage|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/healthcare-uk/about|website=gov.uk|accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref>

Howard Austin Lyons, the former Managing Director, was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] in the [[2016 Birthday Honours]] after launching the organisation in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Howard Lyons awarded CBE for his services to healthcare|url=https://healthcareuk.blog.gov.uk/2016/06/20/howard-lyons-awarded-cbe-for-his-services-to-healthcare/|accessdate=1 December 2016|publisher=gov.uk|date=20 June 2016}}</ref>

