{{Infobox officeholder |name=Liri Berisha |image name= |birth_date=5 July 1948 |birth_place=[[Tirana, Albania]] |birthname=Liri Ramaj |office=[[First Lady of Albania]] |term_label =In role |term_start=9 April 1992 |term_end=24 July 1997 |predecessor= |successor=Lidra Meidani |nationality=[[Albania]]n |spouse=[[Sali Berisha]] |alma_mater=[[University of Tirana]] |children=Argita and Shkëlzen |religion=[[Islam]]}}
[[File:Sali Berisha with Obamas.jpg|thumb|Sali and Liri Berisha with [[Barack Obama|Barack]] and [[Michelle Obama|Michelle]] Obama, September 2009]]
'''Liri Berisha''', née '''Ramaj''', is an Albanian [[pediatrician]] and president of the Albanian Children Foundation, and also an UNICEF ambassador.
She is the wife of [[Sali Berisha]], the former President and Prime Minister of [[Albania]], with whom she has two children, daughter Argita, and son Shkëlzen.
Liri Berisha was born '''Slobodanka Ramaj''', the daughter of Rexhep Ramaj Balidemaj, an ethnic Albanian from [[Martinovići, Plav|Martinovići]] near [[Plav, Montenegro|Plav]], at the time part of Yugoslavia (now [[Montenegro]]), and Milica Bulatović, a Serbian woman of Montenegrin descent born and raised in [[Belgrade]]. After the Yugoslav-Albanian split in 1948, her name was changed by the government to Liri.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.gazetadita.al/korigjojeni-emrin-e-nenes-ne-gjendjen-civile-znj-berisha/|language=Albanian|publisher=Gazeta Dita|date=2015-05-08|title=FAKSIMILE: A e ka korrigjuar më në fund emrin e nënës në Gjendjen Civile, zonja Berisha?|trans-title=Facsimile: Did Mrs. Berish correct her mother's name in the Civic Office registers?|quote=Liri Berisha është e bija e Rexhepit dhe Milicës. Rexhep Ramaj është një shqiptar i Malit të Zi dhe është martuar hershëm me shtetasen “Milica”, mbiemri i vajzërisë të së cilës është ende i pakonfirmuar tërësisht. Por në përpjekje për të mësuar më shumë, zbuluam se në prezantimin zyrtar të kryeministrit të Shqipërisë, zonja Liri Berisha përshkruhet si e bija e Rexhep Ramajt dhe Milica Bulatoviçit.}}</ref>
In 2008, Berisha founded the Mother Teresa Cultural Foundation.<ref>http://capitolwords.org/date/2010/04/27/E683-3_honoring-the-first-lady-of-albania-dr-liri-berisha/</ref> In 2009, the [[Women's Information Network]] named Berisha "Woman of the Year".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://capitolwords.org/date/2010/04/27/E683-3_honoring-the-first-lady-of-albania-dr-liri-berisha/|title=Honoring The First Lady Of Albania, Dr. Liri Berisha|publisher=Capitol Words|date=|accessdate=2015-11-24}}</ref>
Berisha joined [[Autism Speaks]] in 2011 in celebrating the opening of a new centre for autistic children in Albania, calling the centre a way to improve the lives of children with autism there.<ref name="">{{cite web|url=https://autismspeaksblog.wordpress.com/2011/11/30/albania-autism/|title=First Lady of Albania Attends Opening of New Autism Support Center in Tirana |publisher=Autism Speaks|date=2011-11-30|accessdate=2016-12-18}}</ref>
